## Python Modules
What are modules?
A module is a script which contains Python definitions and statements. 
These statements and definitions often consist of existing code that will include functions which can be called outside of the script. 
The use of modules is a great way to package relatable functions that can be called in other script environments. 
One can therefore think of a module as a package with various functions.

## Benefits of Python modules
• Reusability - working with modules makes the code reusable.
• Simplicity - modules focus on a small proportion of the much larger problem, rather than focusing on the entire problem.
• Scoping - a separate namespace is defined by a module that helps to avoid collisions between identifiers.

## Time module example
import time
time.sleep(5)   
print("Hello, World!")
        #prints Hello, World! will be printed after 5 seconds